ce:section.ce:para:
The solubility of GQDs in different polar solvents such as ethyl acetate, ethanol, THF, and water is due to the oxygen-rich groups in their structure. After functionalization of the GQDs with benzylamine, the surface hydrophobicity of the GQDs increased and their solubility in water was diminished according to Fig. 2
                        a. The results confirmed the presence of benzylamine moieties on the surface of GQDs and the hydrophobicity of the structure. According to Fig. 2b, increasing the water contact angle from 30° for GQDs-Amine to 64° for GQDs-Amine-SP is related to the substitution of some oxygen-containing groups with SP photochromic compound and decreasing the surface hydrophilicity (Fig. 2c). According to the FESEM images of GQDs-Amine and GQDs-Amine-SP in Fig. 2d-2i, the nanosheets were randomly joined and twisted in a three-dimensional (3D) framework, with clear wrinkles on the surfaces. The generated multi-layered structure is due to the stacking of layers directly ontopofeachother. Edge torsion can be attributed to the inhomogeneity of the structure after modification with benzylamine and SP. The structure of GQDs-Amine and GQDs-Amine-SP has not changed after functionalization. To define the elemental composition and functionalization degree of GQDs-Amine and GQDs-Amine-SP, CHN elemental analysis was used. 4.967 mmol benzylamine/g GQDs-Amine and 0.582 mmol SP/g GQDs-Amine-SP were obtained. Also, elemental mapping exhibited the uniform distribution of oxygen, nitrogen, and carbon atoms on the surface of the GQDs-Amine and GQDs-Amine-SP indicating the successful stabilization of the benzylamine and spiropyran (Fig. 3
                        ). [37].

According to Fig. 8
                        , in the fabricated photo-responsive material (GQDs-Amine-SP), the FL emission band of GQDs-Amine as the fluorescent donor (400–650 nm, excitation wavelength 400 nm) can be overlapped with the absorption band of the MC as the photochromic acceptor (500–650 nm) formed from the SP molecules manifesting the fluorescence resonance energy transfer (FRET) phenomenon (Scheme 2
                        ). In the designed system, due to the chemical grafting of SP molecules on the GQDs-Amine, the distance between acceptor and donor species is probably less than 10 nm, which allows the suitable overlap and display of the FRET phenomenon.
